1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:08,000
Robotics students often memorize equations
without seeing what the symbols actually do.

2
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:16,000
AxisLab turns those equations into verified,
interactive robotics lessons.

3
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:24,000
Six modules connect motion and coordinates
with orientation, velocity, paths, and forces.

4
00:00:24,000 --> 00:00:32,000
The direct robot lesson works without AI
and provides a reproducible starting point.

5
00:00:32,000 --> 00:00:40,000
Changing d1 translates along its joint axis,
while theta2 rotates the downstream chain.

6
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:48,000
The 3D robot, DH table, matrices,
and end-effector position update together.

7
00:00:48,000 --> 00:00:56,000
Students predict first, manipulate the model,
and then answer questions with real scoring.

8
00:00:56,000 --> 00:01:04,000
Cartesian, cylindrical, and spherical lessons
show coordinate conversion through motion.

9
00:01:04,000 --> 00:01:12,000
The RPY and Euler wrist responds to the mouse
and controlled with three live angle sliders.

10
00:01:12,000 --> 00:01:20,000
Learners compare rotation conventions,
recover angles and spot singularities.

11
00:01:20,000 --> 00:01:28,000
The Jacobian lab maps joint rates
to tool velocity and reveals rank loss.

12
00:01:28,000 --> 00:01:36,000
Trajectory and dynamics labs reveal profiles,
joint forces, and gravity compensation.

13
00:01:36,000 --> 00:01:44,000
A natural-language question can also request
a customized advanced robotics lesson.

14
00:01:44,000 --> 00:01:52,000
The model proposes goals and difficulty,
misconceptions, and bounded parameters.

15
00:01:52,000 --> 00:02:00,000
Deterministic code validates every parameter
and owns the numerical answers and scoring.

16
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:08,000
Generated code is never executed,
and failures load reviewed fallback lessons.

17
00:02:08,000 --> 00:02:17,000
Codex was my partner for architecture,
React, Three.js, FastAPI, tests, and release.

18
00:02:17,000 --> 00:02:26,000
It reviewed the robotics mathematics,
debugged interaction and unified the UI.

19
00:02:26,000 --> 00:02:35,000
The primary build session used GPT-5.6 Sol
inside Codex for the final project extension.

20
00:02:35,000 --> 00:02:43,000
It supported advanced lessons and scoring,
responsive design, and Railway release audit.

21
00:02:43,000 --> 00:02:50,000
Twenty-one backend and twenty frontend tests
verify the current implementation.

22
00:02:50,000 --> 00:02:56,000
AxisLab makes robotics mathematics
visible, interactive, and verifiable.
